Alright...so my mom wants me to at least have picked between these two schools before Hartfords letter comes...and im indecisive adn cant pick for the life of me...so, heres a list of the things i like about Fitchburg

1. its far enough away that my parents have no choice but to let me live there
2. its close enough that, if i dont quit before the year is through, i can go home on teh weekends and work at whites
3. its about a third of the cost of Wentworth
4. they have an au Bon Pain!!!!!
5. they have a very hands on approach to teaching...very good for a visual learner like me...
6. if i decide to change my mind on the whole architecture thing (not very likely)  i can always go into their teaching program, which is also very good
7. the campus is so much nicer than Wentworth's
8. i wouldn't be as afraid to leave campus as i would Wentworth
9. i would have a friend there and i cant guarantee i will at Wentworth (unless Jackie goes), so it will make the homesickness go away faster....hopefully



alright, now for wentworth

1. its only 20 minutes away from btree....so i can visit katie anytime i want...given i dont have too much work to do
2. they are across the street from northeastern...so i can visit ppl all the time
3. its close to BU so i can visit carolyn
4. its a very technologically advanced school...and i love technology stuff
5. i get a free apple computer with my tuition
thats all i can think of for now....feel free to comment on anything thats good/bad/ugly about either of the schools


but it looks like Fitchburgs up by 4 right now

by the way, went to the producers last night with katie and her fam and it was AMAZING!!!!! i kinda wish that we could do that in my lifetime...but ill live in reality instead and just go see it a bunch of times....

i am everything you want i am everything you need i am everything inside of you that you wish you could be..i say all the right thngs at exactly the right time, but i mean nothing to you and i dont know why (story of my life)

i got into fitchburg

yay!!!!

thats all i have to say

no to pick between there and wentworth.........

so life is petty good...im in a strangly odd mood the last week...happy but strange...almost like i feel like im going to wake up and find all of my happiness was only a dream...or that im rushing into thinking that this is a good thing or that im letting the walls down too soon...i mean look at how it ended last time...i just want to be able to be happy and not worry about what tomorrow brings...but its so hard to trust and believe that this is really happening to me, becasue lets face it i dont get too many moments of happiness in my life...but i guess i cant worry and be cautious because ill only regret it later...i dont even know what im talking about anymore...so


to end with a quote

would you look at her she looks at me shes got me thinking about her constantly but she dont know how i feel and shell carry on without a doubt i wonder if shes figured it out im crazy for this girl

well school this year is going to be just stupedious. i really like all of my teachers except mrs. munely, but i think im dropping her class anyways so it doesnt matter.  i sit with chris joyce in APES, which is okay i guess, and rehersals and tech start on monday for pippen.  
  
 
as for life outside of school, ive been chillin with katie darche a lot.  shes really cool...she reminds me of me but a year younger.  and mike, i may be semi depressed right now, but i promise ill be back to my old self in no time..

my mom told me today that if i go to college in or near boston that i have to commute and im not "allowed" to get a dorm.   so thats wicked dumb...and i almost dont want to apply to my number one choice school because of the reaction from certain people, i cant apply to wentworth because there is no fucking way im commuting next year, i need to get out of my house.

work sucks, i need to find someone to work for me on the 25th so i can go to the u hartford open house, but kevin wont answer my text messages, the bastard.  ummm, staceys good, she went ot providence to visit tim yesterday, so im curious to see hoe that went.  and im getting my nintendo fusion tour ricket today! so im wicked excited for that..




and i have a favor to ask of those reading this....leave me a message telling me your honest opinion of me.  im sick of people either pretending they like me, or else being too afraid to let me know for fear that ill kick their ass.  but im bored and curious so...do it you wont...

i woke up this morning and my mom told me that she had to call the doctor about the persistent numbness in her arm.  They told her to come in right away, thinking it was just something wrong with her muscle.  That was at 930. at 1030 i get a call form my dad saying that mom was rushed to the hospital and that he was coming home form work to be with her. i keep twelling my self that it cant be anything too serious, its just her arm, right? but then i think about how close we were to losing her 4 years ago...and i start to panic...


Quote of the day...

because of you, i learned to play on the safe side so i wont get hurt...

i love you mom

this is my third time tryng to post this ss....

I know I said i wouldn't write in this again, but im a little bit pissed off and i need somewhere to rant. I fucking HATE all of the drama that constantly follows me around. Take this whole thing that is somehow still going on after three months (I think we alll know what im talking about).  It should be done and over with.  I mean, I honestly dont give a fuck whether or not we talk again in my life because hes a stupid, immature peice of shit who i,ve come to realize wasn't worth a day of my time. Yet he seems to think that by forcing other people into the situation that i have to like talk to him or regognize the fact that hes even alive.  But what he doesnt understand is that i've changed for the better. Unklike some people i can let go of the past, move on and be happy even without the closure i wanted from our reationship.  On the other hand, hes stuck prolonging something that doesnt need to be prolonged anymore than it has been. he needs to grow up and move on. I really dont even care if thats bitchy of me because its the truth and someones gotta tell it. and i figure i really only have one more year in this shithole of a town before im gone anyways, so i dont care if i have friends or not. ive learned to not let people walk all over me.  So fuck you. 

 on happier topics...I love my friends right now because they have proven to me that theyll be there for me through thick and thin.  They've proved that drama doesn't need to affect freindships.  For christs sakes were all 17 or18 years old now, i think we could grow up a little. 

For all you fuckheads who think that im a bitch or that my emotions are "stylized" at least have the balls to leave a name to go with your prejudiced remarks.  

for all of you who have made me feel like shit, i hope that your happy that youve done this to me. I actually apreichiate the fact that you hate me because its given me the strength to tell you choke on a tater tot and die.

Im just really done with all of this shit. ive moved on, now its your turn...


Quote for today "Everyday si a struggle between what i wanna say and what i should keep to myself. and the words that manage to leave my lips dont hurt me but they hurt everyone else..."
-Everyday, TOBY LIGHTMAN

So yesterday was another one of those great days.  i got a 46 on a listening quiz in french, and was pretty pissed at that.  unless i get like a 100% on the project, im probably going to get a D in her class this term.  then came gym class...and it was soo unbelivably awkward.  me and jennie mac decided to go to the track and walk (as usual) so these two guys are running on the track, and one of them i regognize as the infamous kevin maGardy.  At first, i couldn't tell who the other one was, then I realized it was MIKE HANSON!!!  holy crap, i was like omg i havento get outta here, omg i haveta get outta here...i almost had a heart attack...i couldn't even look at him because i still feel SOOO bad for the way things went down with us last year.  i dont realy feel like i gave him the closure he deserved out of the whole thing.  but im horrible with closure, so...and im sorry to any-and everyone that i was mean to yesterday, for that was the reason for my bipolar moodswings yesterday...then this morning i was a mess.  i was talking to rizzle and cat and nikki about some girl and how shes getting married next year to this "tall, skinny kid."  so im like "well that narrows it down, cause there's NO skinny tall kids in our school" then i turn around and smash right into brendan...figures hes standing over me the whole time im talking...so, yeah everyone got a good laugh at my expense this morning...ill get you back brendan.someway somehow....then im just the dumbest complete mess today and i dont know why...anyways thats my $.5 so...peace and much love
chrissy

so i haven't updated in like a week so... my weekend was amusing to say the least.  friday we finally got mark and mike to come to laff riot...that was amusing, i donminated at mau after.  then saturday i spent with my sister (that was soooo fun....).  then came sunday...so i get a ride to shaynas house from mama curran, and when we get there shayna goes online to see when kevin and anyone else is coming over. so she gets a message from kevin saying he "forgot" it was his grandmother's birthday...shayna was pissed and was like well if you can't come we're just going to make brendan gastby.  so brendan strolls in, with a beautiful new mohawk. after staring at his head in shock for like 2 minutes, we  decided it might be funny to have gastby have a mohawk...that was amusing.  and wyan put on on of his moustaches and started dancing while shayna sang "my moustache brings all the boys to the yard, and there like its better than yours, damn right its better than yours, i could teach you but i'd have to charge..." it was great.  then we taped for a while, brendan and i fought and he ended up flipping me over his head, i got dribbled like a basketball, ate a lot of cheesey bread, and had just a great time.  monday, i went to go see shrek 2 with justine, john, and allan.  amusing, found skittles and popcorn in my pants pockets the next day.  then i came in on tuesday and i thought that mary might hate me cause she didn't really talk to anyone when she came in.  because of my stupidity and lack of motor skills, we didn't talk until today...so yeah my life is amusing, get to talk to my therapist about how much stacey infuriates me sometimes and im going to see harry potter tomorrow @ 6:30 in randolf. if you or someone you know also happens to have tickets to this show, give me a holla... taping sunday(hopefully, gotta grovel at the feet of mama Curran) and grad parties on saturday.  another eventful weekend...woot woot..
